definition.value: Internal capsule is an organ subdivision of the telencephalon which is made up primarily of myelinated axonal neural tissue (white matter). The internal capsule is a major set of fiber bundles lateral to the thalamus and caudate nucleus and medial to the putamen and globus pallidus. It projects dorsally to the white matter underlying the cerebral cortex.

label.value: Subdivision of posterior limb of internal capsule

definition.value: External capsule is an organ subdivision of the telencephalon which is made up primarily of myelinated axonal neural tissue (white matter).  The external capsule is a sheet-like fiber bundle located lateral to the to the putamen and globus pallidus which projects dorsally to the white matter underlying the cerebral cortex.

Extreme capsule is an organ subdivision of the telencephalon which is made up primarily of myelinated axonal neural tissue (white matter). The extreme capsule is a sheet-like fiber bundle located lateral to the clausturm and medial to the insula which projects dorsally to the white matter underlying the cerebral cortex.

Fornix of forebrain is an organ subdivision of the telencephalon which is made up primarily of myelinated axonal neural tissue.  The fornix is an arch-shaped fiber bundle connecting Ammon's horn of the hippocampus with the mammillary nuclei of the hypothalamus and anterior nuclei of the thalamus.
